## Email Configuration

The platform logs verification emails to `instance/mail.log` by default. To use Gmail SMTP:

1. Enable [2-Step Verification](https://myaccount.google.com/security) on your Google account
2. Generate an [App Password](https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords)
3. Update `MAIL_SERVER`, `MAIL_USERNAME`, `MAIL_PASSWORD`, and `MAIL_DEFAULT_SENDER` in `.env`
4. Use the 16-character Gmail App Password, not your normal Gmail password

If SMTP delivery fails, the email is still captured in `instance/mail.log` so registration does not crash.

## Available Commands

Use these commands from the project root. The long Flask form works even when the virtual environment is not activated.

### Setup And Startup

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `py setup.py` | Full first-time setup: MySQL database, venv, dependencies, `.env`, migrations, seed data |
| `$env:MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD="your-password"; py setup.py` | Run setup without typing the hidden MySQL password prompt |
| `Remove-Item Env:\MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD` | Clear the temporary MySQL password environment variable |
| `py run.py` | Start the web app; auto-switches to `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe` when the venv exists |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe run.py` | Start the app directly with the project venv Python |
| `venv\Scripts\activate` | Activate the virtual environment for manual commands |
| `deactivate` | Leave the virtual environment |

### Database And Data

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run db upgrade` | Apply migrations |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run db migrate -m "message"` | Generate a new migration after model changes |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run db downgrade` | Roll back one migration |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run init-db` | Create database tables from models |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run seed-reference-data` | Seed roles, categories, skills, and admin |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run seed-demo-data` | Seed demo users, listings, and exchanges |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run run-maintenance` | Run scheduled maintenance tasks |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run elevate-user <email>` | Promote a user to admin |

### Email

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m flask --app run test-email your-email@gmail.com` | Send a test email if SMTP is configured; otherwise write it to `instance/mail.log` |
| `Get-Content -Tail 40 instance\mail.log` | Show the most recent locally captured emails |

### Testing

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests/ -v` | Run the full test suite |
| `.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests/test_email.py -v` | Run only email tests |

If you have activated the venv, you can shorten Flask commands to `flask --app run <command>`.

## Testing

```powershell
.\venv\Scripts\python.exe -m pytest tests/ -v
```

Tests require `TEST_DATABASE_URL` and use the separate MySQL database configured there.

## Database Management

Use **MySQL Workbench** to manage the database:

1. Create a new connection: `localhost`, port `3306`, user `root`
2. Select the `sahayogi` schema
3. Browse tables, run queries, and manage data

## Project Structure

```
Sahayogi/
├── app/
│   ├── admin/          # Admin dashboard
│   ├── auth/           # Authentication (login, register, verification)
│   ├── credits/        # Credit system
│   ├── exchanges/      # Exchange management
│   ├── listings/       # Skill listings
│   ├── main/           # Home and dashboard
│   ├── matches/        # Skill matching
│   ├── messages/       # Messaging system
│   ├── notifications/  # Notifications
│   ├── profile/        # User profiles
│   ├── requests_bp/    # Exchange requests
│   ├── reviews/        # Reviews and ratings
│   ├── static/         # CSS, JS, images
│   ├── templates/      # HTML templates
│   ├── __init__.py     # App factory
│   ├── commands.py     # CLI commands
│   ├── decorators.py   # Custom decorators
│   ├── extensions.py   # Flask extensions
│   ├── forms.py        # WTForms
│   ├── models.py       # SQLAlchemy models
│   └── services.py     # Business logic
├── migrations/         # Alembic migrations
├── tests/              # Test suite
├── config.py           # Configuration
├── requirements.txt    # Python dependencies
├── run.py              # Entry point
└── setup.py            # Automated setup script
```
